      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">52.211-12</ph> Liquidated Damages-Construction.</title>
      <conbody outputclass="clause" class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3150e8">As prescribed in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     href="11.503.dita#FAR_11_503"
                     base="i1114065"
                     class="- topic/xref ">11.503</xref>(b)</ph>, insert the following clause in solicitations and contracts:</p>
         <p outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps" class="- topic/p ">Liquidated Damages-Construction (Sept 2000)</p>
         <ol id="d3115e25" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3150e19">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            If the Contractor fails to complete the work within the time specified in the contract, the Contractor shall pay liquidated damages to the Government in the amount of <cite outputclass="SingleLine"
                        xtrc="52.211-12_d3138e33"
                        class="- topic/cite "
                        xtrf="GFI">____________ [<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contracting Officer insert amount</i>]</cite> for each calendar day of delay until the work is completed or accepted.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3150e30">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            If the Government terminates the Contractorâ€™s right to proceed, liquidated damages will continue to accrue until the work is completed. These liquidated damages are in addition to excess costs of repurchase under the Termination clause.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p outputclass="Endofclause" class="- topic/p ">(End of clause)</p>
      </conbody>
